Preheat your #oven{} to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} into 3cm chunks (no need to peel). Pop onto a
large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then
toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf for ~{20%minutes} - you'll roast
them for longer once you've crushed them.

While the potatoes roast, quarter the @pear{1} lengthways, remove the core and
chop into small pieces (no need to peel).

Trim the @iceberg lettuce{1/2}, separate the leaves, then tear into
bite-sized pieces.

Put the @wholegrain mustard{17%grams}, @Dijon mustard{10%grams} and
@cider vinegar{15%milliliters} into a large #bowl{}. Add the @sugar{2%tsp} and
@olive oil{2%tbsp} for the dressing.

Season with salt and pepper, mix together and set your mustard dressing aside
for serving.

> See pantry for sugar and olive oil amounts.

When the potatoes have cooked for 20 mins, remove them from the oven.

Use the bottom of a #bowl{} or pan to lightly crush each potato.

Drizzle the smashed potatoes with more oil, then return to the top shelf of
your oven until crispy and golden, ~{10-15%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pop the @Serrano ham{8%slices} onto another baking tray.

Bake on the middle shelf of your oven until crisp and golden, ~{5-7%minutes},
then set aside.

Add the lettuce and pear to the mustard dressing, toss to coat, then stir
through the smashed potatoes. Share the salad between your #bowls{}.

Snap the Serrano into shards and serve on top along with a sprinkle of
@crumbled blue cheese{30%grams}.

Enjoy!